This paper deals with the computational problem of finding stable models of a knowledge base, which is a fundamental problem in artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves logic and complexity theory, which suggests cs.LO and cs.CC as likely sub-categories. The use of classes and hierarchies in the paper may also relate to cs.DS. Finally, the paper deals with logic programming, which is a topic in cs.PL.
